# Culinary Dash — gitignore

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# THE DEV BUILD. NEVER COMMIT THIS.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# culinary-dash-devtools.html is the built file with DEV flipped true. It is
# byte-identical to her build except for one flag, which makes it exactly the
# kind of file that gets shipped by accident. It's regenerable in one step
# (cd build, flip the flag), so there is no reason for it to exist in history.
culinary-dash-devtools.html

# Harness scratch (cd test writes here)
culinary-dash-work/
game_script.js

# Logs from the G2 setup
g2.log
pd-install.log

node_modules/
.DS_Store
*.swp

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# THE BUILT ARTIFACT. Ignored deliberately — see DECISIONS.md.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# It inlines all 22 art blobs and changes on EVERY commit, so committing it
# would store ~800KB of unchanged art per commit. git dedupes art/*.b64 by
# hash (unchanged = free); the built file defeats that. Committing it undoes
# the readsafe split in history-space while preserving it in context-space.
#
# It ships as a GitHub Release asset, tagged per delivery. That's where a
# built artifact belongs: versioned, downloadable, out of history.
culinary-dash.html

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NOT IGNORED, DELIBERATELY:
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   art/*.b64  -> build INPUT. Required. See .gitattributes.
